The paper deals with the problem of reconciling two sets of data, which is a common problem in databases (cs.DB). The solution involves error correction codes (cs.IT) and has implications for distributed computing (cs.DC) and communication complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) for efficient computation and communication.
